tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly decreased creatinine, which is not clinically significant and may reflect low muscle mass in an elderly female. No evidence of renal dysfunction, electrolyte imbalance, or abnormal glucose metabolism. Overall, laboratory findings are unremarkable.
